TikTok
TikTok as a social media provider is provided by the following entities:
for users from the European Economic Area ("EEA") and Switzerland by TikTok Technology Limited, 10 Earlsfort Terrace, Dublin, D02 T380, Ireland, for users residing in the United Kingdom ("UK") by TikTok Information Technologies UK Limited, Kaleidoscope, 4 Lindsey Street, London, EC1A 9HP, United Kingdom, for US citizens by TikTok Inc., 5800 Bristol Parkway, Suite 100, Culver City, CA 90230, USA, and for all other countries: TikTok Pte. Ltd, 1 Raffles Quay, #26-10, South Tower, Singapore 048583.
The TikTok pixel we use is a JavaScript code that helps us track and understand user activity on our website. It collects information about usage and the device used, referred to as "event data." This event data includes: descriptive page metadata (e.g., page title, product information, key parameters such as value and currency), page performance data (e.g., page load times), button click text and elements (e.g., button name, descriptive text, and attributes).
We use this event data to target our ads and improve personalized advertising. To do this, the event data collected on our website is transmitted to TikTok. Some of this event data is stored on the device you are using, and cookies are also used through the TikTok pixel to store information. However, this only happens with your consent. You can revoke your consent at any time through the "Cookie Settings" on this page. The collection and transmission of event data are carried out jointly by the provider and the respective TikTok entity. We have an agreement with TikTok regarding this processing as joint controllers. This agreement defines the division of data protection responsibilities between us and the respective TikTok entity. In this agreement, we and TikTok have agreed, among other things, that we are responsible for providing you with all information about our joint processing of your personal data in accordance with Articles 13 and 14 of the GDPR and that TikTok is responsible for facilitating the exercise of the rights of data subjects in accordance with Articles 15 to 20 of the GDPR. You can see further information about this agreement below, and the document is directly accessible at
https://ads.tiktok.com/i18n/officialial/policy/jurisdiction-specific-terms
.
The responsibilities of us and TikTok in the context of joint processing are divided as follows here.
The aforementioned TikTok entity is the sole controller responsible for processing activity data after its transmission. For more information on how TikTok processes personal data, including the legal basis on which TikTok relies and the options available to data subjects to exercise their rights against TikTok, please refer to TikTok's privacy policy at:
https://www.tiktok.com/legal/page/eea/privacy-policy/en
